# Chapter 8 — Pattern matching

`match` deconstructs by shape. When the shape fits, the bindings on the left become names on the right. When no clause fits, `match` errors with a rich record — Chapter 10 covers those.

## Match on lists

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(match '(1 2 3)
  ((a b c) (+ a b c))
  (_ 'nope))
</pre>

## Match on symbols

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(define (traffic-light c)
  (match c
    ('red   'stop)
    ('yellow 'slow-down)
    ('green 'go)))

(traffic-light 'red)
</pre>

## Rest patterns

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(match (list 1 2 3 4 5)
  ((first . rest) (list first rest)))
</pre>

> **Sakura says**
>
> When the runtime says a `match` failed, look at the `expected` field of the error record — it lists the patterns that didn't fit. Nine times out of ten, that tells me exactly which case I forgot.

